<TITLE> Fire-fighter injured in multi-storied building </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 5 (bdnews24.com)  A fire fighter was injured while struggling to put out a fire at a building in the capital's Green Road area on Monday. The fire broke out on the second floor of the nine-storey building at around 11:30am and was extinguished an hour later, Abu Nayeem Shahidullah, director general of Fire Service Station told bdnews24.com. The injured fire fighter 'Dilip' was rushed to hospital, he said. The building known as 'Green House', is the location of many diagnostic centres and doctors' chambers. The fire might have originated from chemicals which are kept in one of the laboratories, Shahidullah said. b
